    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="963"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d963">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/24278a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Ambassador of Brazil</gloss>
                    </hi>.<note n="35" xml:id="d963fn35">The same to the other conferees.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 9, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: I enclose for your information
                    copies of the communication<note n="36" xml:id="d963fn36">Not printed; it was
                        revised at the meeting of August 11. See the telegram of August 13, 6 p.m.,
                        to Mr. Parker.</note> to the chiefs of the factions in Mexico, such as the
                    Conference agreed upon at its last meeting.<note n="37" xml:id="d963fn37">The
                        meeting of August 5 (see the Secretary’s July 29).</note> As you will
                    recall, it is proposed to send this communication to a number of influential
                    persons in Mexico, a preliminary list of which was prepared by Ambassador Suárez
                    and is being considered by me with a view to ascertaining whether any names
                    could be added. * * *</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
